\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid10362445 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 John Hughes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Wern, Llanfrothern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your not married are you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, I'm not, no, I've never been married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 1901. October 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Next door to Plas Lllandano in Llanfrothen. In the Orangery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How many years did you live in the Organgery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 For six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I went to Garo Gano, that was the name of the place. I was there for five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I went to Garreg. Next door the Post Office. And I was there - for twenty-five years, yes, twenty-five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember why your family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well in the beginning the house went too small. We got a bigger house in Garo Gano and then a bigger one still when we moved to Llanfrothen. I had two brothers and a sister and as the - the family got bigger we had to have a bigger house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the ages of your brothers and sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I had one brother older than me, my sister younger than me. She died when she was twenty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the other sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Sorry, oh, I don't have - I didn't have another sister. I had another brother younger than me. That's right, one brother older and one brother older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I don't know. I haven't an ide
a. My father died when he was sixty-five and he'd been - and he's been dead for thirty years, which makes him twenty-five when he married. Married. Yes, he was a young man when he was married. My mother and father were the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh he came from Ciernganarvon. From Allaspandy, next door to the woollen mill. And my mother came from Llanfrothen, from Fedel Llanfrothen, where Ned is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What was your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh he worked in the quarries for a long time. A
nd then he went back to the farms. He was working in Nysor with Llwellen Jones, he was there for thirty-two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 That was all the jobs he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, that' was all. Yes, yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, no, nothing. He couldn't read or write. My mother could read but she couldn't write. They were totally illiterate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes, I do. Yes, yes, he was out of work - he couldn't get dole or anything then, it's a very hard time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother have a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, she worked on - on the farms. As a servant on the farms. Yes, she did work after - after she was married. Listen to this, this is what she did. She was - worked as a far
m servant. No, she worked for farm servants who were employed for six months and she did their washing and that for about two pounds a - two pounds for six months.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When your mother was working after she was married who looked after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh we looked after ourselves a lot after we'd grown up. Yes, well after we'd reached about ten or twelve, but even before that we had to - we had to look after ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I'd like to ask you about your life at home up to the time that you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, when I was at school you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How many rooms were there in your house in the Orangery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, I don't remember anything about that. I only remember about the house in Garreg, there were three bedrooms there and a room at the back 
and a room where we lived. Now I don't remember anything about the first place, there were two or three rooms there, I'm sure. Long thin house. It was like a flat wasn't it. There wasn't any upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there anyone else apart from your brothers and sisters and your parents living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, there weren't. No one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother have anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, no one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, it was - it was - it was done in - in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother or father sew clothes for the family and mend for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
My mother used to knit, she wasn't really one for the sewing but she knitted very very well. She could knit a pair of socks in a - in a day. Yes, 
she was very good. I can remember things like that, you know, talking about things like that. My sister was the same she grew up. She died when she was twenty-seven you know
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were most of your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, we tried to get - you know, new clothes when we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did you buy them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - Penrhyn or Portmadoc.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When did you do this - was there a special day or a special time when you went to buy clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, we used to go when my father had got a litt
le bit of money from the - payments, the special payments, monthly payments, extra bonus payments from the quarry, or - or from - from his pay at the end of his six months term on the farm. When money came in, that's it, that was the only - really the onl
y way we could get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, the same, the same thing. We used to - so that we used to get shoes at the same time, we got clothes. Yes, sometimes we got shoes and paid for them later. They were big strong shoes. Yes, big hob
nail boots they were. Oh yes, I remember. I remember children still wore them when I was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father help your mother at all with jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, sometimes. Yes, sometimes if mother complained and things like that. He didn't as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he do anything for the children, did he dress you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he give you baths or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, he told us stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, he couldn't read. Yes, he told us story of his life and things like that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, we went to Port and things like that and went for walks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have any jobs to do around the house as children, special jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, we didn't really have very much, we - mainly we just played. Especially after school and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the other children, did they just play too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, but my - my sister she spent a lot of time in the house, she knitted and things. My mother had taught her to knit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did the older children help the younger children with things that they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, they did you know but - and t
hen what really happened at weekends was that I had to go out to work to earn a couple - a shilling or two. Yes, I went up to - up to Rothy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have to go to bed at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, about nine, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who put you to bed, just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, mainly my mother, but sometimes my father did too. Oh yes, my father would do that, I mean, we had to go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How old were you when you first went to bed on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - I'm sure I went to bed when I was about five or six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you share your bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, with my - my two brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 There were three bed rooms weren't there, one for your mother and father and one for your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Which room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh there wasn't a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you have, just a bath tub in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, in - in the living room. I mean, there wasn't - there weren't any baths anywhere in those times were there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did you have to go into the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh well - once a week, every - every Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh every week. Oh yes, we had to have clean clothes every week, my mother believed in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did the family eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - they ate in the - in the back kitchen. Yes, that's where she cooked and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there any time when you had your meals in a different room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. When we had visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean to put on a show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes. We got the tin of salmon out when visitors were coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of cooking equipment did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh the - there was only the - the coal fire. There was nothing for it but the fry - the frying pan and the saucepans and - you know, we cooked potatoe
s and - and that you know all on the open fire. I mean there was nothing like electricity or anything then. But it was - I mean, it was good food anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh well, I mean, I didn't really live very far from the s
chool did I. I had breakfast about half past eight. And then school started at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the other members of the family, when did they have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh, my father ate his breakfast about six before he went to work. And my mother had her breakfast with him then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh well - I mean - my mother made - bread and milk. And the other thing is I don't know how to say it, it was called maith wyl, it was made with eggs and bread and things. It was a very
 good thing anyway, maith. Yes, it had a lot of milk in it. It was a very old recipe, I mean, nobody makes it now. But it was very good anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have anything special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Anything special for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Just for lunch then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, for lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What time was lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well - midday. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was everybody there at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, everyone was there. Everyone was there including the dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you have usually for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Just an ordinary day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh we didn't really have very much to eat at - for - for dinner at lunchtime. We had dinner in the evening when my father got in from work. That - that in fact was the time that my mother m
ade a - a meal for us all, made dinner for us all. We did go home from school and have lunch at midday. But then, we only had a cup of tea and a piece of bread and butter, something like that. I mean, that was all we could have really. And then we couldn'
t afford very much food really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about Sunday? Did you have anything special on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, we got - a lot more meat and things on Sunday. It was a really go dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. My mother baked - baked bread.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about making jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, she made her own jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she bottle her own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, she did a lot of that too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she make pickles too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, she made pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, she didn't - she didn't make wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, she used to - make - make medicine for sort of childish illnesses and things like that. It was something from the land, sort of - herbs and leaves, things like that. Oh yes, yes, my mother made things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was any beer made in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, not in the house, my mother was against beer but - my father was quite willing to go down for a half sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they grow their own fruit and vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, when we moved out of the village and went and lived on this little farm, Llandrniog, we had a bit of land, yes, my father did plant things and - potatoes and swedes and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they buy vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, before that, yes, all vegetables were bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have any tinned vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, very few. There were very few in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they keep any hens or anything lie that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, hens and pigs too. Wh
en they killed a pig we really had enormous feast. It was very nice. We salted the pig and then we had bacon and ham and things like that. It was hung upside down after it had been pickled.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 It was very nice then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 The pig? Oh - my mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did you have meat in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh about two or three times, no more. And then some weeks, very little and sometimes not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh we had very little really, sometimes some corned beef but not very often. Salmon was the thing my mother believed in. Tinned salmon.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever have extra meat like rabbit from poaching - who went after these rabbits and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh me when I - when I'd grown up and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no. No my father never went. No, my father never really was much of a pocher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I went very often. Once I'd started to shoot I went shooting wild ducks and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you ever remember your mother giving herself less food in order that the family should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. I do remember, I must admit. When my father was out of work things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she give more to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, and to all of us. Yes, I must admit that. It's a terrible thing to say, but - you know, that is how I remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, certainly. It was very homely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you ever allowed to choose what you had to eat from what was cooked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, sometimes, but - but, you know, more often we had to accept what my mother had cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And you had to eat it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I don't suppose you would leave anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did your parents say when you left food behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh - they said we were wasting, you know, we had to eat it all. We had to have some excuse for it - that we were ill or something, you know, in order for us to be able to leave food behind. There was one thing that I didn't like
 and that was - bread and milk - sour milk. I was always ill when we had sour milk pudding for - for a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt, were you allowed to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, we could ask - ask and then wait.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you ever allowed to ask for a second helping of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, my mother liked it when we asked for a second helping. As long as there was enough of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they expect you to to hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, my mother did. My father wasn't quite so particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you ever allowed to bring toys and books to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no. Yes, well may be we were allowed to bring a few books but - not toys. Anyway we never had 
any toys. I mean, I was ten years old before I had a bike. And it was - after my brother that I had it anyway. No, we never had things to play with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, we could. Well we had to say but then - but then again sometimes we didn't say, we just got up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did all he family sit down at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, everyone together. And if there was a visitor there he came up to the table too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did everyone have the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, everyone - all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who prepared all the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - my mother did. My sister helped, you know, when - after she'd come to a certain age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In what order were you served at mealtimes, who had their food first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 O
h - I think it was my mother and father. And then us afterwards, I mean, it was still the same table. And then again maybe it was us first and my mother and father second, I can't really remember. Anyway, we all ate together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did your brother and younger sister eat before they were able to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh, they sat on my mother's lap and she - she fed them. Goodness, have I got to answer all those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was your mother an easy person to talk to, if you had any worries about anything could you go to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, very easy, yes, you could go up to her and tell her your worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes - my father too. I mean, they were very - well, you know I didn't have anyone else to tell my feelings to apart from
 them. Yes, I mean if I had problems at work and I didn't like a particular farm, I'd tell my mother and father that I wanted to leave, but - well in fact they always persuaded me to stay. In order that I shouldn't be out of work. I had to carry on for - 
for six months. And then change the - change farms after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have to show respect?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, we had to show respect, we had to look up to them. We weren't to cross them in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your brothers and sisters, were you allowed to fight with them in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 We - I yes, there was one brother of mine that - was always fighting and our mother used to come between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You weren't allowed to sort of hit back at each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, not at all, not if she could stop us we couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped that you would grew up to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well, my father wanted me to go and - work on the farms, I mean, tha
t was his life and he wanted that for me too. But on the - other hand my mother wanted me to go into the quarry. She thought that they were too - the hours were too long on the farm. And in fact I went to the quarry and - I sistened to mother but - I was 
only there for three weeks. I didn't like it there, I went back to the farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents bring you up to believe that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well - they wanted me to live - morally, and things like that. Because you see I ne
ver married. I mean, they wanted me still to be - very moral in order to go on to live in the life afterwards. Oh yes, they were very like that you know. Only - I didn't live - I didn't listen to them very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no, no, we couldn't swear, we couldn't swear. The biggest sin against my mother was to swear, and my father too. They never swore themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When adults were speaking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, not very much. No, we couldn't do that
 because I mean, they were talking and we weren't. We couldn't cut across them anyway, that's sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - sometimes my mother spanked us. Yes, a good spanking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh my father never beat us, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did your mother give you a beating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh not very often - thank goodness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember a particular time when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I do, I remember going over 
to the estuary to swim, paddle. And my mother had told me that I couldn't go because I'd been ill. She was frightened I'd get cold and catch pneumonia or something like that. I got a pretty good beating that time. I'd really sinned against her that time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh I felt pretty cross. I didn't want to talk to her for a long time after that. But then I mean, she was my mother after all. And it was really my fault because I hadn't listened to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both parents or from either one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh from both. From both. Oh yes, I must say that, yes, I mean, I got - all my information from - from both of them. They disciplined me you know, told me wh
at to do and what not to do and - I listened to them a lot when I was young. Yes, I had to lie to them sometimes though, if something had happened to me, I mean if I'd fallen over and hurt myself I - had to pretend that it hadn't happened. I had to say th
at really. To stop them, you know, telling me off afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about birthdays, were birthdays different from every other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they were. We had panclkes on birthdays. Oh yes, yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No.
 No, none. The only present I ever had from my mother was when I was 21. I got a cigarette case full of cigarettes, I remember that. That was the only thing I ever had from mother that is, but - from my father I got a bike. I was about - seventeen then. I
 mean, that was before - I mean - I got my present from my mother when I was twenty-one and I had a bike from my father - before. It was a bit better then, there was - they were working more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, we had a party and - two or three of my friends came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you all sit round and have pancakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes. And then - when my sister was having her birthday - her friends came in, and when my little brother had his birthday, I mean, his friends came but - everybody was round the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember doing anything special with your mother or father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No. I don't really remember Christmas Day being very different from any other day, except of course for the lunch. We had - a hen or a - a duck 
or something like that. But then we did put our stockings up for Father Christmas but we got very little really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Didn't you get anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, there was something, there was an apple or maybe an orange or something like that. But nothing like toys or anything like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about musical instruments in the home, like pianos or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, there was nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there anyone who sang in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean in my family? Yes, my sister could sing quite well - not - not well but it wasn't bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no. No. Not me, I'm still the same you should know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Neither your mother nor father sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But - my father was from a family of great singers. He was also from a family of -
 people who recite poetry. No, my father wasn't really very talented at all. I mean, after all he hadn't had any schooling. He'd never been to school. No, no, no, he hadn't. I mean, maybe a week or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, there were some games at that time. Snakes and laddes and ludo. And a game of rings. And that was really about all we had in the way of games. We hadn't heard of cards or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there any books in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, a lot of books. Oh yes, a lot of books. My father - collected books for me and my sister because we could read. Yes, it was us that got the books and my mother used to buy us lots of books when she could afford it. There was a man who came round 
a long time ago - who sold books from door to door. Yes, old books, I've still got some of them. Daniel Owen and people. Stories of the Fireside. And Gwyn Thomas. They were very interesting. My mother knew that I liked them and - my sister read a lot too.
 And poetry books, that's what she used to get me, and I still like poetry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh there weren't many. Oh yes, the Herald Cymraeg. Herald Cymreeg. Welsh Herald. We had that every week. And I went home to read it t
o them. On a Tuesday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your mother could read, did she ever read out aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no, not very often. Sometimes she'd read to my father but he'd always say - you're making up a new Herald for me. 'Cos I used to go there and - and read it after she had. Read it out aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh goodness, yes. Certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of thing was it,?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean my father's funeral, that's what you mean is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your grandparent's funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, I don't remember my grandparents' funerals. No, I don't remember either of those. The first funeral that I do remember in the way of a relative of mine was a cousin - was that of a cousin of mine who was killed in the quarry. And that was the funer
al. He was about twenty-two or something. Or twenty-three. He was killed in the Crysa quarry. It must be I mean about forty-one years ago that he was killed. And he - a bridge gave way underneath them. And two people were killed. And that really was the f
irst funeral that I felt sad at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did a lot of people go to this funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
You mean the funeral of this boy who was killed in the quarry? Yes, a lot of people - it was a very big funeral. Yes, I mean it was more of a funeral because he had been killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they wear special clothes at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes of course. Black clothes. Yes, a black tie and - bowler hats and that. And then - my father was the next to die. And after my - father, my mother, then my sister and then my younger brother
 and my older brother. And now they've all gone, there's only me left. There's only one little man left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents take you to visit with friends and neighbours and relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they did. Yes, I mean every six months I went wit
h my father to see his family. To see his brother and his brother's wife and things. Nyspandi was the name of the place, you know, by the - woolen mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents take you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, they did, specially if I wanted a new suit or anything like that. I had to go and be measured. And the same goes for shoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You've already said that you used to go out with your father alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I used to go very often with my father. But after I'd grown up and I was - I'd started w
orking, 'cos very often it was my mother who went with me shopping to find clothes and things like that. 'Cos I had to get enough clothes to last me six months, so - she used to come with me then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you ever remember going on trips with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. Yes, I went - I remember going to Llanbedrog on the Sunday school outing. We always went to Llanbedrog. We never went anywhere else - oh, except to Barmouth. Yes, those were the two places we went. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 It was just Sunday school trips you went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. Yes. On Saturdays. Yes, we used to collect the money on - on Sundays and if there was enough money gathered together we'd go off and - and have a trip on the next Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember going on holiday anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean when I was at home? Oh - on, only - only to my father's family. Yes, I mean it was three miles away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh only usually for about three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did all the family go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, just - just me and my - me and my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you spend Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
You mean when I was at home? When I was small? Ah - when I was small - you know, up 'til I was about nine I used to play. But when I was ten or twelve - I went to work - to work on the farm. That is on S
aturday. Yes, I used to go and earn about a shilling, it was better really than playing. To be earning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I went to chapel on Sundays three times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have to wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Sunday - Sunday clothes. Yes, and we even wore them to eat and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your parents felt it was wrong did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes, definitely. Oh yes, they were very religious. No - it wasn't really that, it was just respect for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Which denomination did your parents belong to - which chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh to the Methodists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they attend chapel every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, my father went every Sunday but my mother not quite so often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, I went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You went on Sunday school trips? Did you ever take part in any other social activities connected with the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes. Things like - small meetings. And we had to learn things 
for that, like a piece of recitation. I mean, it had to be something like that, I couldn't sing, so -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You weren't in the choir then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, I wasn't in the choir so it had to be recitation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember things like the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, I remember every Tuesday night we went to Tanlan to the Band of Hope. Now it's a house of course. Yes, we did things like competitions to see who read the best poem or - choirs and things like that. Yes, learning poems and singing - I mean
, there's a wide variety of things there. Drawing and things. Everything like that. It was very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there any other clubs connected with the chapel that you did belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, nothing like that. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you say grace before your meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no. No, I didn't anyway. I mean - I did - I did say - say prayers before I went to bed. I still do in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have any sort of family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No. We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Very little. In fact hardly any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you know what his ideas were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, I do in fact. He was a great Liberal. He wasn't a Tory and he wasn't Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there Labour then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I think there was. Yes, it was j
ust starting then actually and - yes, that's what my father was, a - a Liberal. Haydn Jones was the man then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you feel towards his ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I was right behind him, all the way. And we used to play wicked games at the time of the electi
on, a lot of them. We had a down on the Tories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of things did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Ah well - there was this old man, John Jones, he used to live in Tanlan. Yes, and he was a big Tory. And we went there, three of us, Willie Moran and Emrys. They're
 both dead now. And we used to call out after him, things like that. And then - we used to call out, hey and John Jones the Tory. Old John Jones the Tory. And in the end we threw a brick through his - window. And we broke a wardrobe. And - remember it was
 
a very poor time, and my father or mother had to - had to pay for this wardrobe and the window. Oh yes, but it wasn't only me, there was the other two too, as well, it was a combined thing. We used to provoke in that sort of way. Oh it was a terrible day,
 
election day, in those days. We used to shout down to George Morris, he was a great Tory then. He used to live in Rachynys. And then we'd say, up with Haydn Jones. Send George Morris to the pig sty. Yes, I mean I can remember things like that. Those sort 
of things are very much alive in my memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your mother, did she take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no. Not at all - not at all. Yes, my - my father was just a bit you know but we did at least know that when he went towards the school 
to - make his vote as it were, you know, we knew which party he was going to vote for. We knew that Haydon Jones was the man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother go and vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, she went to vote. And I'm sure, you know, he was the same, yes, the Liberal. 
Yes, because I mean they were both great friends so - be the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
At that time some men felt they were endangering their jobs by voting in the opposite way to their employers, do you understand what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember that sort of pressure being brought to bear on people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, yes, I do. Yes, I know that, there were people who were afraid. Yes, I mean, you know, when I was working on the farm in Nysfor, I mean, the Nyscor people, they were - big Tories. But
 even then my father was a Liberal, even though he worked at Nysfor. He wouldn't have any of it but - there were other workers at Nysfor who - who did - you know, who were f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4683318\charrsid16455207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ightened. And they wouldn't vote against the employer. Yes, they - they were frightened - frightened of losing their place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But then nobody should really know by right should they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, they shouldn't but - they still brought pressure. Yes, I mean they were behind a lot of things really weren't they. Very often.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was your father ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, never. Because after all he was illiterate so he'd be good for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your mother wasn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father work for the Liberals during the election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No
. No, he didn't. But then again I mean nobody really worked for them then I mean except people who had a car, and there weren't many cars then. I mean, everyone walked really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember your parents taking part in anything political outside election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean when my father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, and also in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well I mean you know he was in the house and he used to gather a
 bit of wood to put on the fire, get a good fire going. I mean, you know, he'd do that in the day 'cos there wasn't any - very much money to get - get coal or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother have any particular interest outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, not really, not very much. I mean, she used to go out to work, you know I've already said that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember her going out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who did she go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - usually with her sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What time did your father get back from work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - he went about six and he came back about - seven. And - you know, and how had quarter of an hour's walk on top of that - from Nysfor. Yes, I mean he was home between half past six and seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he stay in in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No doubt - no, he - he'd go - sometimes he'd go down for a quick half. When he had the money of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 So he went to the pubs did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well - yes, sometimes, not - not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Your mother didn't go though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no. My mother never - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father play football or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, nothing. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well he used to go to the horse and dog show in Portmadoc at that time. We used to call it the horse and dog show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of things was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh well, there were horses there and dogs and cattle. I mean, they called it the horse and dog show. Yes, that was - that was in May. She used to go there. And my mother went to, that was the only trip that we ever went on together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father bet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father or mother ever belong to a savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No, they didn't. The only thing that my father did to save was not to smoke. He never smoked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards your brothers and sister, did you feel anything special towards any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, not really, we were all friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - I never played with my brothers either. No, no, I used to go and play with other friends. I used to play a lot-in Tanlan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Whereabouts did you play? In the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, in - in - in the street and - in the fields and that. Anywhere where we were allowed to go really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Could you go to the other childrens' houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh we used to play an awful lot of football. And swings, I mean we used to swing on the trees. Yes, we used to play more football than anything else really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you allowed to get dirty when you were playing, did your mother punish you for getting dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, she did really. She didn't like us to get dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you free to play with anyone you wanted to, they didn't say that one particular friends wasn't suitable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no, no, not at all, no. Oh yes, you know, it was - very free in those days. But then I mean it's the same today really, all children play with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever belong to a youth organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. Oh yes, I did. The Boy Scouts. I belonged to the Boy Scouts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh it was very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well we did drills and that and - I was on the drums for a bit, you know, there was a - there was a Boy Scouts Ban
d. In fact we used to practice in Plas Llandano, Cloughs home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was Clough there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - he wasn't living there but - he used to come there sometimes. And this bloke called John H was the Scout Master. John H Griffiths. And he was the one who us
ed to drill us and he'd take us for walks sometimes around up by Aberglaslyn and over to Prenteg, like - in a form of a march really. Yes, I suppose there were about eighteen to twenty of us there at the time - at one time. And then they got this band tog
ether and - it was only a small one but - I was on the drums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever have any other hobbies, did you have any animals or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean when I was at home? Oh yes, yes, I had a - a dog, a sheepdog for - for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you train it or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no, no, I had nothing to train it on. This of course was when I was a little boy. Yes, he came round to our house one day and - my mother told him to - told me to send him home you know. And I chucked a stone after him and h
e - picked the stone up and brought it back to me. Yes. And I mean that was the end you know. And I mean after that, you know, he couldn't go. I had him 'til he was an old dog, he was a yellow dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember going fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well - I remember - poaching, but not - but not fishing. I was a great poacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean you only fished illegally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember going for walks or cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean walking a - a lot of miles? I
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I mean up mountains and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, we used to go up the Moelwyn very often. That's the only place actually, we never went up Snowdon. Yes, we used to go up the Moelwyn. Yes, there was a group of us going you know, and - well actually we used to go up the Moelwyn
 with the schouts. A form of practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you yourself take part in any sports, you said you played football, anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. no, not really. Yes, I mean, there were - when there were sports, say at the time of the Coronation, we used to hav
e races and jumping and - things like that. Yes, I mean I liked interests like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you ever remember going to a theatre, music hall, concert, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean when I was small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When you were still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, 
I can remember going to pictures. Yes, I remember the silent pictures. It was only - all silent then. Yes, I used to go to Penrhyn to the small hall there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you given any pocket money by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, sometimes but - you know - not very often, sometimes a - a shilling an a Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of things did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well to tell you the truth actually, I spent most of it on cigarettes. Yes, I've been smoking since I was about nine years old actually. I don't know that it done me all that much harm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember friends or neighbours coming in and helping your mother in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, they did and - and so did neighbours and that. You know, there was much more of a feeling of community in
 those days. Now, you know, people want money for being - for being communal as it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember what happened when your youngest brother was born? How did your mother manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, she - she managed all right. She got friends - she got friends in and - to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents have relatives living close by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, my mother had two sisters living nearby but my father's brother was some distance away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How often did you see these relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I saw them - these one
s - all the time. I remember one old aunt of mine who - buried her husband when she was young and she had five children to look after. One of the sons was one of the boys who got killed in the quarry. And there were four others. No, no, there was six in a
l
l. And she lived without any charity at all. And all she did was - was sell a bit of firewood, she'd take them with the horse and cart - from - from Llanfrothen to the - to Penryn to the town. Yes, she lived on - on this firewood, and - all she got for ta
k
ing all this firewood, done up in bundles, to Pentyn was about two shillings. Yes, she went all the way from Vedu, you know, it was a hard time then. The things was she said that she was never - never going to ask for charity from anyone. She was determin
ed to bring them up on her own, I mean, it was a hard - a hard way but - she wanted to do it on her own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your parents, did they ask their friends into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes, they did, there were a lot of - a lot of our friends up - up there at the house. Then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes. Yes they did. They were always the same friends. Oh yes, I mean the - the house in Garreg - it was - always full of farm workers and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father and mother have special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. My - father was particularly friendly with farm workers and quarrymen and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your father go out to visit these friends and did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, yes, they did go, both of them. But - but I mean we weren't really interested in these friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You've already said that these friends were invited into the house, how often did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - very often they used to come without invitation. They just come you know. And I mean they were welcomed in exactly the same way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were they offered things to eat when they arrived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, all the time, every time. I mean, if there was food on the table well - that's it. They had some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 The friends who were invited, were they both your mother and father's friends, they could both invite your friends around?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes. Yes certainly. I mean there was no difference between them - between them. 'Cos I mean after all it wouldn't do for my mother to give more more of a welcome to her friends than - than to her husband's friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did neighbours drop in too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. All the time. They were very neighbourly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 They tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, have you any rec
ollection of plays of forms of entertainment that people did themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - I remember more when I got older. Yes, after I'd left school, when I went to be a farm worker over towards Brickley, that way. Yes, I was there for five years and the mos
t sort of interesting thing we did there was to go to the the loft - the loft above the stable where all the - farm workers slept, and we used to amuse ourselves there. We used to sing old ballads, things like that. Yes, we used to sing and - sing ballads
 
and - funny songs like Mochyn Du. I mean they were called loft songs. And there were - there was the odd boy who had a great deal of talent. And then I - I remember - a certain Hogan Goch, he came from over Tanibwich way, and he was really good at singing
 these old ballads. I don't remember them now, I only remember that - at Hogan Goch, the Red Haired Girl, was one of them. And the girl who was rejected was another one. Yes. It was - very interesting you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 A lot of people divide society up into di
fferent social classes or groups, do you understand what I mean, sort of working class and middle class, upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean like poppa vald, big people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 People being upper class or middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, yes, it was rather like that
 then. Yes, there was a class that wasn't as high as the second class. And then above that the first class and that. And they didn't really have very much to do with people who were a bit poorer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that you yourself belonged to a-y particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, I wouldn't say - we got on with all sorts of people. Only there were people who weren't the same. I can't really say but they were more classy. More of a class. They didn't want to have anything to do with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of people would you say were the same as you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well the people who lived in - in the village. Yes, and - and all around really but you know - you know what there - there were in Llanfrothen, these sort of big farmers. I mean they weren't really in - in our cla
ss were they. Yes, the people lived in - in small house, poppa pentil, all they had was the roof over their head. And - they - they were all the same class. They - they were all very similar. Yes, I mean think of the people in Penhue at that time, I mean,
 they were all the same class as my mother and father. I mean, all people from Garreg, only there is one - yes, there was a - a certain person, I wouldn't like to say who she is but - her parents, her mother and father, were a bit above us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember being brought up to respect some people and not others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I remember we had to touch our caps to - big people, big nobs you know. Yes, even - just passing in the street, you know, we - through - going through Garreg we had to touch our cap
s, and we did this up to very recently. Yes, we had to do that to Miss Sybil and Miss Minnie. And I'm not ashamed of saying that you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 There's nothing to be ashamed of - most people had to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, we had to do it. Yes, and we had to sir them. Yes sir. You had to say yes sir, yes sir, until you choked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I remember the old master at Nysfor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you actually have to call him master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. Yes I did. And the old lady of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have to show respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, yes, we did you know. Father and mother. Especially father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But you didn't say sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, no. Not a - it would have scared the life out of the old man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of people were considered important in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - wait a minute - the shopkeepers. That's one. Yes, yes, they were quite important, the grocery people. And then there was another man who sold the coal. The coal merchant. 
I mean, he was considered to be a - a bit important, quite important. Yes, anyone who was it any sort of - business I suppose - selling things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And then I suppose there were poppa vald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, yes, there were, I'm afraid I must say about 
these people at Nysfor. They were really the only class we had around here at that time. I'm afraid the old Major Roach would kill me if he heard me saying this. Remember to knock this out off the tape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you know why these people were considered to be important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, I do yes. I think it was because, you know, we thought they had a considerable amount of money. Yes, it was money. And seeing that they had animals, you know, sheep and cattle and - horses. And I mean they would have been considere
d important even if they'd only - only had these animals and no money. And I mean there were a lot of other farms too you know, big farms. I mean, you know about them. And there were a lot of sheep and cattle and I mean - you know, those farms, you know, 
we looked up to the farmers there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of people did the shopkeepers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh they had - they had to mix - they had to mix with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the ministers, the preachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they - they were quite good - good at mixing in with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they had to. I have to say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, the farmers had to too because they were - quite often seeking information from people who understood farming,
 you know, like my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about employers, factory managers, things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh - oh yes, we did - we did look up to them highly and I mean they didn't really mix with anyone. You know what I mean, how should I say this, I mean the worke
rs looked up to the - to the managers an awful lot. I mean, I remember - although I don't really understand about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15288850\charrsid16455207 q}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
uarry, about - these two people in - Festining who failed to - carry out the contract by the end of the month, it was a very wet place or
 something, and the head steward came past and said, I hear you haven't been able to complete the contract. And they said, yes, I mean we haven't managed. And he said, well actually you're two very ordinary rockmen. And one of them replied, well and you'r
e
 a pretty ordinary steward too. In fact I could tell you an awful lot about the quarries although I've never actually worked there. I remember there was an old man called Robin Jolley from Festining. He was going to look for work so he went to the office,
 
knocked on the door. He knocked on the door, goes in and says, any chance of a job here? And the steward says - how did you ask, he said. He was a very high man. You sit here in my place, he said, and I'll go out. And so he went out and Robin sat down. An
d
 he came in and said, is there any chance of a job, please? And Robin looked at him. I'm afraid your hair's too white, my silver boy, he said. Yes, I mean that was the thing, they - they didn't look up to them but they were frightened of them. I mean, you
 know Robin, he didn't - he didn't care about them at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of people would you say usually went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well I'd say people that were very similar to each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were they different to you, the chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well yes the
y were, they had more - yes, there was more - sort of - morality, discipline in the chapel. Because say for instance a person - a church person got drunk one night, I mean, all you'd hear is that - he got drunk, that's it. But, you know, if that happened 
i
n the chapel you'd be thrown out of the society. You couldn't stay behind. But then I mean there were quite a few who did walk out - the chapel. I mean the chapel got used to that, but then they had to - quite often you know the people wanted to be re-acc
epted back into the society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that in the village all the workers had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they did. Most of them that is. There were a few who had - more sort of interest in gardening, and others who - you know,
 went down for a pint to the - to the pub. I mean, that sort of difference of interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you think that at that time there were some workmen who felt that they were in some way a cut above other workmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, I wouldn't say that at all about the workers. I could say about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2364651\charrsid16455207 
craf}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
t workers though, the craftsmen. They were - they did feel themselves to be above the labourers. I mean, say the rockmen in the quarries set their sights higher than say a labourer did. And because of that I didn't like
 it when I was working in the quarry. I didn't like other things about it either. The work and - things like that. Yes, I mean it's - it's still the same - there's still the same split between craftzmen and labourers in the quarry at the moment. Oh yes, y
es I'm sure there is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes they did. As I said to you, they both looked up to people above them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember your mother feeling that she belonged to a particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well - how do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she see herself as belonging to a working class or a class a bit higher than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I mean she didn't - no, she didn't feel - she didn't - like people who - in some way felt that they 
were above our family and looked down on us. Because I mean they knew that really they - they were the same class as her. And her - and my father. All that had happened is that they'd had more luck and more money. They didn't like, you know, like those so
rt of people. At least, that's how I remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember if it was possible at that time to move from one class to another? Moving up or down, do you know what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I mean - do you mean classes with more people in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 To move up to a higher class, to improve yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - in order to do that you need to have a lot of friends. I mean friends and influence. Well that's my idea of it anyway. I mean, you know, think of my father, a farm labourers in Nysfor. I mean, he became fri
ends with his employers and in a way they respected him, they - they - they respected him and of course he also respected them. But even then, you know, he was still the labourer. The servant. I mean they had a - great amount of - sort of feeling for them
 but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember any particular person who did improve him self and move up the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, I do, I remember a lot of people liked that. I mean, think of people of my age. Now - some went to be bankers, one of them's a banker
 in Uganda. William Henry he was, he's dead now. Yes, and then there was Arthur, he was in the same class as me at school and he went to - London to a - a milk place, a milk factory. Yes, and then there was - what's the name - I'll tell you, he used to be
 
uncle of Gwyn the garage. Yes, he got a very good job, something to do with geography, in South Africa. Yes - yes, he was - he was at school - school with me, he's done very well, he's still alive though. That's the sort of class that you mean isn't it? I
 mean - and - and - I mean, the same class as me who've - who've gone - gone up, who've - who've improved themselves. And then there were the girls, some of them have grown up to me nurses and matrons. Oh yes, yes, in my lifetime, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In my life do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Or didn't you use those terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, yes, we used to say you know main real good vonhevig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember why this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, it was when somebody was - kind to the poor. I can really only say that much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember seeing a policeman in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Goodness me, yes, many many times. I was frightened out of my wits by him. I used to run away as soon as I saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did he treat people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh he was pretty stern. Very stern indeed. I remember a bloke called Gitso at school, he was the same age as me, they say that Ghitso saw a policeman while he was at - still in school. He saw him through the win
dow of school and he escaped through the window and ran up to Dinask and Tothengwn. It's a fact you know. He was frightened for his life of the policeman. And maybe I shouldn't be saying these sort of things either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, a very small rent from Clough Ellis. Fair play to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you see much of Clough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean in those times? Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, he was always coming up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh we looked up to him very much. Ye
s, he used to give us a party you know. You know, he still gives parties for the children and - we had parties there - his house. And there was a big pole on the - on the tower, up there, above the village, and there was a flag on it to - tell everybody t
hat Clough was at home. That's what the flag was for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember your parents having problems in making ends meet at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, many times. When my father was out of work and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well I felt sad. Well I mean we had to feel sad because we couldn't get anything without money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did it make a great deal of difference if your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, it did. Certainly did. Because I mean there was no dole or anyth
ing to be got. I mean - I mean what was there to - to have, there was nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You never received any charity or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, nothing. Nothing. No, we lived - frugally. Morally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 If there was somebody in your area that people disapproved of, was there any special way of showing this disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, there was, I mean, to the extent that they were - distant from us, I mean - they were far away from us. They didn't want to do anything with us. And that showed that they didn't want to be friends with us and we didn't want to be friends with them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about people that you didn't want to be friends with, that you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - well - we just weren't friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In some areas they have what's called rough mus
ic in which a great deal of clatter and noise is made outside the house of a person who's behaviour is upsetting people, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes. They used to do that. Yes, they used to do that too. And they used to knock on doors and knock
 on windows and things like that, and make fun - fool around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
If a family had fallen out with another family they'd send the children - it was the children really that did the naughty things - not the parents. But they were taught to do it, the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have any lessons from your parents or a private tutor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, none at all. I was only taught in Welsh, there was no English at school. I was very good at going to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How old were you when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I was thre
e. Yes, I used to go from the Garden House, the Orangery as you call it. When I was three. And I'll tell you who took me, Hannah Ellin, the mother of Gwyn the garage. She says she used to carry me every step of the way. It's her that's been telling me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What time in the morning did you set up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 About five to nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And when did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh about half past three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of school was it, a day school, boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, that's right. I was really happy at s
chool. I went there for four years at one tie without losing a day. And I got a watch for doing that as a present from the Merioneth Education Committee. Yes, it had written on it - presel berchaun, which means full attendance, 1908-1912. I remember it no
w. I don't know where the watch is but I remember the engraving. There was - there was three of us who'd been, you know, who'd stayed at school the same. And then one of us went on to - get a gold medal for seven years full attendance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about going to school, did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, it was only five minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did anyone go to school with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, the children from the village mainly, from - from Garreg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you eat at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I ate - I ate at home but som
e bought - some bought food to school, rough food. Milk and bread - sour milk - and bread and things like that. And buttermilk and they'd hand it out in - in little cups. That is between brothers and sisters from the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards the school, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I was - I was - very happy there. And I really liked it, I mean, if I hadn't have liked it I wouldn't have gone there would I. And I - I went there when I was thirteen. I left there when I was thirteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards the teachers? Did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no, I didn't - I didn't like the teachers, especially the one that had had me in the last year. He was always after me for something - a certain Jone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2364651\charrsid16455207 s he was called. In the end he a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 nnoyed me so much that I kicked him up the arse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember the teachers emphasizing things as being important like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, very much on manners, I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And being on time and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Very much, very much indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 If there was something that the teachers disapproved of in your behaviour what happened? Did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, they punished us terribly. Oh they beat us badly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Even girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, girls exactly the same. Ye
s, there was this particular teacher, you know, old Jones was the headmaster but there was this other man, Pierce. He'd take hold of us by the heads and bang our heads together - until we were completely stupid. And he'd do exactly the same to the girls t
oo. He was cruel. They were too cruel in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of things did they punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh for anything. Any small thing. For instance if we went to the sale in - in Garreg and we were about five minutes late - 'cos I mean there was a f
air in Garreg, an animal fair - and since we were children we wanted to go to the fair. And I mean if we were five minutes late getting back to school I mean there was the most incredible row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they did, a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they ask about what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, we got like - todays children get - we got a report at the end of the term. Oh yes, they took a great interest in the reports. I mean, and they had a reason for going this because - because they were ille}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2364651\charrsid16455207 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 rate themselves. And therefore they took more interest somehow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they ever go up to see the teachers to talk about you and your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, well the only time that they did go up there was when 
I'd been badly beaten at school. I mean, they didn't go up for anything connected with my work or anything. It's just that my father was very angry, very - angry that I'd been beaten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did the other children at the school come from similar homes to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, they did, nearly all of them. Yes, we were all at the same - level, all of us. But I mean, there were some farmers children but I mean, we looked on them the same when we were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did the teachers have particular favourites in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about you, were you one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember any gangs at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh you mean like - doing wicked things - together? Oh yes, yes, I do, a lot of them, yes, yes, I'm afr
aid I was rather in the gang - that did naughty things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there any children who were left out of everything and no one was friends with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well no, not really. Not really. But I'll tell you one thing, there was this - boy who was very ill
. Yes, he was the brother of Idris you know. Yes, yes. He was called Rhys. Yes there was something the matter, he was - he was too ill to play and he died when he was eighteen. There was something inside him that didn't grow as he grew. And I remember a v
e
ry - strange circumstance with him. He used to get chilblains, terrible chilblains. Yes, chilblains on his - oh his fingers. And I remember one situation - I mean we liked him enough but he couldn't - he couldn't play with us. And I remember old Pierce, t
h
is old teacher. he couldn't - he couldn't hold his pen because of his chilblains, he couldn't hold the pen in the correct manner which the teacher was demanding. And he came with, you know, one of those sharp - rulers and he said, put them fingers down. A
n
d hit him across the knuckle. And he fainted - I mean, Rhys fainted now. And - his fingers were blue, you know, he - it was - it was the chilblains. And I don't want to say about me but I threw a bottle of ink and hit him on his forehead. Yes - I did. And
 
one time three of us attacked him. And that time the policeman came and - to see us. His father came. And - but even then nothing - nothing happened. Because they felt that in a way we had defended him. Because - because in a way they were blaming the tea
c
hers. The teacher - the particular teacher - for what had happened. And - they never forgot that about the teacher and the - and the - the - the mark of the ruler was on - on his hands. And I mean, it wasn't his fault, it was just the situation of a - of 
a - of a sick boy. And I mean really they should have made a favourite of that boy. He couldn't help how he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You only went to the village school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, that's the only school. And I went up to standard seven. And I left there when I was thirteen. Wasn't bad was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 If you'd had the opportunity would you have stayed at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No I wouldn't. Because I wanted to go out and earn for my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you go to any further sort of part time education or evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. I used to go to evening classes to improve my reading. Reading Welsh that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you regret anything about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I've regretted an awful lot that I didn't go further ahead. Yes, yes, I've regretted that a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you think it was good for you, it was worth going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, yes, I really do. I mean - I mean where would I be if I hadn't learnt - I don't know what I'd do if I hadn't learnt to read. But still I couldn't do man
y sums in those days. I can do from far more sums now than I could when I was school. No one can do me now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When you were at school you had a - apart time job on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I used to like to go to work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh I got it by going to ask - ask the farmers. Yes, I used to go to different farms and sometimes to Nysfor, my father was there. I'd go and clean shoes, things like that. I didn't really work on - on the farm that much. And then I used to have to go and 
do the gardening and I - ran away then 'cos I didn't like doing the garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How many hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh only on Saturday - all day Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How much did you get paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh a shilling. A shilling for a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel that this was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well no, no, but I was glad to get it. No, it wasn't fair, it was terrible. But then - we were pleased to get anything. I mean, we were pleased with tuppence in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, she got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did she buy with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - everything. Oh yes, she'd buy anything and - every ha'penny was a great help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you like the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I did. Oh yes I did, I liked them and I - liked the
 - the people in Foty very much when I went there to - as an agricultural labourer. Oh yes. Old Sian Edwards and Ann Richards. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But that was a full time job wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes, yes, full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did your employers behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh, not very well. Not well. Yes, some were very rough. They didn't - they couldn't see that - they kept feeling that we weren't doing enough and there we were working from six o'clock in the morning 'til seven at night and we were just young bo
ys. And you felt - angry towards - this. Oh yes, yes. I mean I'd just get up and go after half a year. It was great to see those half years come to an end. We worked on this system of - being hired for a period of six months. And if we didn't stay there f
o
r the full six months we wouldn't get paid anything at all. Yes, it was - I mean, it was like selling yourself, I mean, on a lease. And this is what they used to do, they used to - say you promised to go there for ten pounds for six months, they'd give yo
u
 a penny a week or something like that. I mean - yes, it was - they couldn't have given you a shilling 'cos if they'd paid you a shilling a week - it wouldn't have kept there 'til to end of the six months. I remember - I remember saying that I'd go for si
x months to Kevin Ko-ch, and then I regretted that I'd gone, but I'd have had to have paid out five pounds to leave. And of course I went there, I mean, it was better than paying out five pounds. And I didn't - I hated it - hated it there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your first full time job, that was in Foty wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I was really happy there. Very happy indeed. Taking the horses to be shod and - milking and working with the sheep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What hours were you working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I got up early. Six about and sometimes worked through 'til ten. That is when we were making hay and carrying hay and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You did work on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. And Sunday, yes, Sunday too. That is - Sunday in the winter. We only did the minimum on Sundays and - there was only r
eally there milking to do. And feeding cattle in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How much were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh - I got - you know, two pounds for half a year. And then ten bob on top of that if I pleased - them. And I'm sure I worked very hard for those then shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel that this was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No. No. No, surely - not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How were your employers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh they - they were fine. Fine. They were very kind. Oh yes, they gave me clothes, clothes and - handed down from the master. That's
 where I got my first paid of long trousers. Oh I was really proud of myself then. With my hobnail boots. Oh yes, they were very kind to me there. I still think a lot of Owen Jones now. I must say that, I'd say it to his face and to his back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards the work, you part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I was very happy. I - I felt - very well towards it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did this part time job change your attitude to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I didn't feel like going back to school so much after that, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In your job in Foty did you ever have paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, there was no such thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When you were working in Foty did you give any of the money you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. The whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You were living in Foty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I was living in and I get paid every six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And then you gave it all to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And she spent it on all sorts of things did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. And she used to spend quite a lot on buying clothes for me. But I mean it wasn't very much was it. it was only two ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How would you say you got on with the people in Foty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh very well. Yes, they were - very noble people there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you actually like the work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. I mean, I was learn
ing there, I was learning to cut hay and learning to cope with the - the horses and the cattle. I mean I had to learn didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did this full time job change your attitude to school, did you regret leaving school after you started this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh y
es, I did. Not so much in Foty but it was - after that you know. Years after. Yes, I regretted then that I hadn't really stuck at it at school. I mean I could see myself, I couldn't really speak English anything. And then I mean I learnt a bit you know. W
ell like I am now in fact. I mean I didn't learn any of this English in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How many servants were there at Foty, just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, there was only me - except for - in the summer they had ka scyther to scythe down the hay.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did you eat there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh in the - in the kitchen with the - with the master and mistress, we were all together. And then I mean I used to sleep in the house too. In a bedroom, you know, up the top there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there anywhere you could sit when you weren't working, a sort of private place for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well no, no, only in the house with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did the master overlook you while you were working and instruct you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, yes, he did, he watched me and he was pretty hard sometimes. He used to expect more than what I was capable of at thirteen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel happy amongst the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I was - very happy. They were kind to me there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you call them, did you call them sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no. No, I called them aunty Sian and aunty Ann.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the master, what did you call him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - Owen Jones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel that they took an interest in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. I did. They were very kind - very kind to me. I used to get pocket money from them somet
imes on a Saturday. You know, a shilling or so from them. They were very kind that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they offer you any sort of guidance of how to live a good life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, they did because - con}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4273879\charrsid16455207 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ider if I was at home on a Sunday - I mean - with old Sian Edwards, Aunty Sian, I mean I had to read the Bible. Had to read a chapter and verses and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have any time which you could call your own, spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Only really at night time. And in the evening. Or else I'd go over to see the - the - farm labourer - the other one over in Tanygwyn.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Could you go and come from the house in your spare time as you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, and I could go home to my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they mind what time you got back in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh
 yes, I couldn't be very late. Oh yes, I had to be in the house by ten to ten thirty. But, you know, I was young then. And they used to worry that I might have got into some - well you know, it was a very lonely place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you homesick for your family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I was in the beginning. I used to cry a bit I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel lonely because it was just you working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, and I'd been so used to being with children. And, you know, I was missing the children for a reaso
n. I was particularly homesick when I - just when I'd - gone to bed. There were times when I couldn't get to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there anything particular that you didn't like or did like about your situation there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean, didn't like doing? Well the 
only thing I didn't like, doing was milking the cows. That's really the only work I didn't like, you know, I didn't like milk. Only I - you know - I very much liked giving the food to the cattle and being with the horses. But I really wouldn't like milkin
g, I mean, that's the only job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who did the housework in Foty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - both of them really but - Ann Richards I mean, she did the most. Yes, she'd sew a bit you know and she used to sew for people outside and sell - sell things she'd sewn. And they washed and everything like that in the house, oh yes yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh it was - old Sian it was, she did most of the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who did things to the house if it was sort of falling into disrepair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes - you mean sort of decorating and things like that and - oh - Ann Richards, she did that. Yes, she was very good with her hands.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they have any children at all there in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, there weren't. Old Sian Edwards was a widow and - they never had any ch
ildren and - old Ann Richards was a spinster. But they were two sisters. But - they didn't have the same surname of course, 'cos of one being married before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did Owen Jones fit in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh he was the son of a sister of theirs, Margaret Jones
. Oh yes, and he'd been taken - he'd been - taken when he was ten to be brought up by them. And he'd therefore become the farmer there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did they eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh on - on the big table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, there only was the kitchen and then there was a sort of pantry at the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of equipment did they have for cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, only the fire and the saucepans and the frying pan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did every meal get eaten in the big kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, every one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was everyone present at breakfast dinner and tea and supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes. There we used - everyone - we used to be up by about six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of food did they eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, the
y used to eat sort of - country food. Bread and - bread and milk, sour milk, buttermilk. You know, buttermilk from - the - the stuff that's left after - after the - the butter's been taken off the - after churning. And then we used to put milk or cream on
 top of the butter milk. And a bit of sugar of something on top of that. It was nice, very nice, I liked it a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh we had - quite good dinners and potatoes and meat - but not every day. I mean sometimes it was just off you 
go, you know, and we'd have - bread and milk again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh we'd have quite a good supper. We used to have a cup of tea at about four. Then a - a butty and some - a bit of jam. And then we'd have supper, sort of cold meat and thing
s like that. Or friend bacon and egg. Yes, I mean it was a - it was a good place for food. I must say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have anything special on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, we had a special dinner on Sunday - midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about things that were actually made in the house, bread and jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, everything, they made everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Pickles and even wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, not - not wine. Or beer. No. Only jam - well I mean, when they killed a pig or something they'd make faggotz and btawn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they make medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes. They made - a sort of herbal medicine. I can never remember exactly what they did but they used to get some sort of herbs from - from the - from off the walls, and they used to get a lot of medicines from that. And they had some
thing - you know - wkarts, they had a special thing for - for - for removing those. Some special round leaves. I don't really remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was it like some sort of magic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, it wasn't magic 'cos you actually rubbed it on your hands. But I mean 
it did work. Oh yes, yes, it did work. I mean, they believed in things like that - and you believed in things with them and then of course they went - the things went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who actually prepared these thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - old Sian it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Where did fruit and vegetables get grown, in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, there was a sort of - enclosure - orchard place. There were a few plum trees but - are they still there now - but I don't think there were any apple trees or anything like that. And then they planted 
potatoes and had a few carrots, swedes and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they buy any amount of vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, they had to buy a lot. And - especially in the - the time after the holiday, after Christmas. When the things that they had grown had finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What animals did the family keep on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - mainly milking cows and rearing c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4273879\charrsid16455207 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 lves and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Had they got any sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes. Yes, there were a lot of sheep there. Well - yes, about a hundred, a hundred and fifty sheep.
 And then - horses, two horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there for sorking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Who looked after these animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, well me on the whole. Well, actually Owen Jones used to do quite a lot - more with the - with the horses because he h
ad more experience than me. Because I hadn't - practiced plooghing or anything like that's 'cos I was too young. And in fact he did most of the feeding - of - of the horses, but of course I had to do it when he wasn't at home. I used to - in fact I used t
o have to fed everything then. He used to go over to Porthmorna quite a lot. And therefore I had to be around you know to - to feed everything, feed all the animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How many times a week would you say meat was eaten in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh not everyday. Three or four times a week probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they use any tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, none. Except on very rare occasions when - when - there was some corned beef there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you given the same food as the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, exactly t
he same. But - since - sometimes the women wouldn't take - bread and - and milk pudding. Only the master and me would do that. And I'll tell you, there was another thing we used to get to eat there, they'd kill an old hen and we'd have a - chicken - chick
en to eat. For - for dinner. It wouldn't matter if she was old even. And really tough, yes. Having been running round the yard for years. Yes, we'd just boil it up before we reasted it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember anything that the family did together on Christmas Day or were you at home on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I was at home on Christmas Day. Ye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4273879\charrsid16455207 
s, I was allowed to go home at C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 hristmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they play any musical instruments there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, none at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And they didn't sing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, when we all went down to the village they - they'd sing - when they were out as it were. That is not - not - not the young boys but you know, the older ones, they sung carols and things. And I mean that was ; very interesting. You know the farm Er
w
 Fawr - above Aberglaslyn there. And if - if the people in the village were singing on a fine night they could hear right up in Erw they could hear the voices coming across the valley. You know, as the crow flies. I mean it's quite a lot isn't it. I mean,
 
it's a fact you know, because Frank Hughes, you know, he used to live in Tylabach. Yes, Frank told me several times that he'd heard them. Yes, it was when we were by the church they could hear the voices, it - it went across like the waves of a sea. It wa
s interesting. It was interesting to - to hear somebody from Erw - saying that they heard us because - as far as we knew nobody heard us except the - in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, a lot. There wasn't a single Eng
lish book though, only - only Welsh books. I'll tell you what there was though, there was a - a book called The Travells of a Wanderer. No, not a wanderer, a pilgrim. And it was there in Foty that I read it. And then there was the Stories of the Fireside.
 I mean those were their books, and then of course the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Could everyone in the family read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. Yes. Everyone. Only - very - they were very pedestrian at it. And I mean you know, just 'cos I'd had schooling I was - able to read a lot better than them, even then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, they - they took the Herald, the Herald Cymraeg. Oh yes, and they took the Hedegis too. That was another paper, a weekly. Yes, it was a - it was a weekly paper, it came somewhere from - I 
think it was up in Frestiniog - Blaenau Ffestiniog. And that - that one came on - on a Wednesday night, it was a sort of small paper, oh it was only about a penny or something. And the Herald was a penny too. But, you know, there was a lot of news in the 
Herald, from everywhere you know. Garreg and places like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no. No. None of them. No, other was never any - there were never any magazines, there may have been some but no one had ever heard of them in Foty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they read aloud in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes they did. Sian Edwards used to read out aloud a lot. And I used to read out aloud with her. I mean take, take a chapter from the Bible. I would read the first verse and she - read the second one. Yes, we use
d to go - one by one like that through the chapter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember a funeral at all in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh I remember the funerals of both the old ladies. But - I'd left by that time. Yes, I'd gone away to live but - I went to the - to - to bury both of them. Even they'd left Foty by the time they died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever go out with the master or mistress on a Bank Holiday or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 The only place I'd go with the master was to some sale or other. You know, cattle. But it was a fai
r really, not a sale. Yes, and the other place I used to go with him was to the horse and dog show in Portmadoc. I'm sure I've said about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You used to go to the horse and dog show with your father as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, and I went with the - with the master too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Could you describe to me what happened in a fair, what sort of thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh it was very interesting. You'd hear them auctioning - bargaining and clapping their hands. The clap meaning that they'd - finished a bargain - made a bargain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were all the sheep and cattle sold in this similar sort of way, in these fairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, then there was a fair in Penrhyn a long time ago you know. And the cattle would be lying happily in the middle of the street. And then ther
e was another in Penmorvan, Tremadoc, and everyone would come from everywhere - it was nothing to see a - a couple of hundred cattle there at the sale. Especially at the fair in Croesor, that was a very big one. That was the first fair of summer that was.
 
When they sold the animals. But then there's another fair following six weeks after the first fair or summer. And they mainly sold horses at that one. Yes, buying horses to - to help with their harvest. And then there was horses going away to work on the 
railway lines in - in England. Yes, and - buyirs would come and - and buy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was this where the agricultural workers were hired, it was a hiring fair wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, there was a - a fair in May which didn't have any cattle or anyt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991511\charrsid16455207 
hing, it was just a - a hiring f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
air for - and people starting off on their - their six months stint. And - and women too of course. And particularly the one in. Pwllheli, this was the most popular fair. It had the most people there. The girls would stand on one side of
 the street and the men on the other side. And then the farmers would come along and ask them if they were staying where they were or wanted another place, looking for another place. But - for me, I mean there was only one time which I - was hired in this
 
way to go somewhere else. And then I didn't go there. I was supposed to go over to the other side of Duffryn. There was a fair in Harlech then. And - and that's where I was being hired, that was the fair for me. That was when I was supposed to go to Duffr
yn but my mother wouldn't let me go because it was too far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I must have been about seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you like going out with the master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, it was a sort of treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever go with the master for a short holiday or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No, never. There was really no - talk of holidays then. You just worked all the time. I mean holidays are very new invention really.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your master and mistress believe that it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, they believed very much in that. The only things you could do were essentials. Yes, f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991511\charrsid16455207 arm work like - feeding the cows}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207  and milking the cows. Just feed - just feeding - feeding all the animals. But - nothing else. I mean, we couldn't even chop
 wood or anything like that. That was - I mean, that was part of their religion really. Their faith.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they go down to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, they did. Ann Richards went anyway but the old lady, I mean, she was - she was too old. She used t
o go, they used to go - they - they went to Croesor you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I - I went to chapel all - he time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they go every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did Owen Jones go to chapel too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - some
times. But - I had to go - I had to go every day to Sunday school. I mean - I liked going really, I mean, it was a sort of break for me. And - afterwards I'd go to visit - Magya Nones, the mother of Owen Jones. And have tea after Sunday school. It was a t
reat really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she live in Croesor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. It was a treat really - for me to go away from Foty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were you allowed to sit with Owen Jones in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, certainly. It was their seat - in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you say grace before meals at Foty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No we didn't. Only before I went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. No not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you know what they voted at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes I do. The old lady was - a Liberal. And Owen Jones was a bit 
of a Tory. And you'd say he's still a Tory probably. Well I don't really know, you can't really tell but - I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember them ever talking about the danger of people losing their jobs if they didn't vote in accordance with their e
mployers wishes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. Yes I do. Oh yes, I remember - I remember people endangering their jobs. They wouldn't keep - if they were - a servant didn't please - a servant had to work. And they used to discuss that a lot. And if he refused to work then - then he had to go.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But they minded if he voted in a different way to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh no, no, nothing like that, nothing. But if he didn't work he had to go. That was the reason they had to go. Because a scyther came there for the summer for the hay
 sometimes, and if he didn't scythe so much hay in a day, I mean, they knew on the first day how much he was doing and he had to go. They wanted to a good man. And - they paid a little bit more money to a scythere in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean more than a farm labourer would get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, because they only fame cor six weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did the master take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, he would sometimes when there was a tug of war on or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 So they had tugs of war then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, there was a few games like that sometimes. Oh yes - jumping competitions, high jump and long jump.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was this a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, not really, it was just a Saturday afternoon thing. Yes, I mean - do - you know - the - old people or older peopl
e, that's what they did, they did things together. But then there was something for the children too. They things I remember is running in sacks and - three legged races. And really it was something to entertain the children really. But then the men had t
ogs of the war and there was great fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you have tugs of war between one village and another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, between us and Penrhyn and - no, mainly between us and Rhyd. Yes. Oh and there was a - a football team from Rhyd a long time ago too. Llanfrothen and Rhyd used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Owen Jones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. Yes. Horse races you mean? Yes, well actually I - went - I took part in a horse race at the horse and dog show in Portmadoc. And I wond with this horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was it a horse from Foty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes. And Mrs Stubbs helped us. She remembers it very well. And there was another man from - who lived in Park then taking part but I won. I was about fifteen then. See I was growing up and I was getting experience with horses then. I e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 ven remember the name of the ho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 rse, Tommy. Oh it was a very interesting amusing time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were they big horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, he did keep a couple of - a few ponies. Riding ponies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In Foty you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. Yes, to ta
ke - to take him down to the village and back. Yes, that's right. Yes, we had to go and fetch the doctor to Penrhyn on - on the - on the back of the - the pony. Yes, I had to get up in the middle up of the night to go - to go and get the doctor when someo
ne was ill. And I was afraid. I had to go at two in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And it was you who always had to go was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, it was me. Yes, it was very heavy times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they play cards at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, there was nothing like that. Th
ere was only sort of - ludo and things then. I told you that before. But then there was - how Foty was and - but I don't think they could play cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did Owen Jones go to the pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, he'd go - go down for a pint. And he still goes doesn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about the two women, did they ever go out on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - when I went there the old Sian Edwards was really to old to go anywhere. But Ann Richards went to Croeser and Penrhyn and - but not very much. I used to take her with the horse and trap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did she have any interest outside the house, any hobbies or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No. Not many. Neither of the two did. Sian Edwards in a way had more interest in the farm. And she used to tell me how to - manage the - pigs and the cal
ves and things like that. But the other - I mean, she didn't know anything, she didn't know anything about the farm. Only, I mean, old Sian Edwards was a bit of a farmwife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 They didn't do any work for charity or anything like that did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, 
no. Nothing. No, there was nothing like that but if there was - for instance - some children in need, they were very kind that way. Ann Richards'd make clothes and things - for poor children, small poor children. That was really like charity in those days
 wasn't it. I can't think what else it would be called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they all go out together at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, very little. I've already said that - old Sian didn't ever go out. Well, I mean, obviously Owen Jones was a farmer wasn't he.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he ever go away from the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, and I'll tell you where he went. He'd go to Wrexham to but horses. To buy two horses, him and another old farmer who lived in Garreg Vale. Robert Roberts his name was. Yes, the two'd do, they'd go on the six o'clock train from Penrhyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How long did they go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh they came back on the same day. And they'd get back in the - deep into the night. And then the horses could arrive the next morning. They came on the train to Penrhyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did his absence make any difference to the way the houses was managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
You mean when he was away? Well - we all tried to do a little bit less on the odd day. Well I did anyway. I used to run riot more than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about Ann Richards, did she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. 
No. I didn't really - bother with Ann Richards - but - Sian Edwards was the one that I was most frightened of. And if there was somebody there working on a daily basis, well I had to stick to work then, 'cos they'd see me. When he - when he was away that 
is because there was this - little man that used to come from time to time. To spread the muck and things like that. And I had to go with him, he was - Davy Jones was his name, David Jones. And he came from Tanygrisiau.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did he come all the way over from Tanygrisiau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. He was - a roadman on the whole. And he used to come all the time. When he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 nted a job, isn't it. No, David Hughes was his name. And he used to catch me out sometimes. But then, after he'd got a bit of money he'd go down to G
arreg again, have a few drinks and then he'd start singing. David Hughes spreading the mux}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
, spade and fork one by one, alternately. Oh you - you make me remember things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about if Ann Richards was away from the house, did this make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. It was more homely with Sian Edwards. I had more freedom. I think - yes, yes, it was freedom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did they have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, a lot of friends. They had very good neighbours. Their neighbours were very good fr
iends. Yes, they'd go down to - all the farmers round about. And specially shearing day, that was a great day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you go over there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, the - neighbours were very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you go and eat in the houses of the neighbours? On special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I'd go there but - not particularly on special days. I mean, if I went over there for a walk I was sure to get supper or something there. I was just passing sometimes and I'd just - you know - call in. There were no sort of parties betwee
n the neighbours then. No, no, there was no such thing. Oh only when there was a - birthday or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was there any singing together, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No. Not in Foty. Only in the stable loft. I've told you about that before. But then the
re wasn't a stable loft there, I was - I slept in the house. But then there is - there is a loft above the stable there actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of event was a birthday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh they made a bit of pancakes. Made pancakes. For whoever was having their birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was it farmers mainly who came to these events?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, mainly, but there were two sisters of Evan Jones who came there. They came on their holidays, they'd been working in London. No, in Birmingham. And they were really the only - tw
o - well they weren't really strangers 'cos they came there every summer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that the people who came were all from the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, the same class, all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Which class would you say that is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well it was a class that could get on with everyone. They weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean snobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no, nothing like that. They were people who were very easy to live with. And they looked down - looked towards their servant as if he were - one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 They respected the servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
As long as the - servant respected them. I mean, there was that in it. Well it had to be like that because - if they found a - a servant who told lies he wouldn't please. It was a very small think in fact that threw them. That - just wouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that the master and mistresses showed more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 espect to some friends than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no, I wouldn't say that, they were - the same to everyone. But I mean, that's just my opinion. I mean, I never saw them showing any favouritism towards anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did the people came to the house treat the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh well, exactly the same. Yes, and it was very homely. I don't know what other word you could use for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that your master and mistresses were content with their lives or did they want to get ahead, go further?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - I'll tell you what. They wanted to - to get a - a bit more money. Yes, because Owen Jones has gone ahead hasn't he. Oh yes, yes, he did. Yes, he made a - he made money in th
e end. He's been a - a big dealer. And do you know the first thing he ever bought? A billy goat. That was the first bargain he ever made. The old dealer. Do you remember how he talks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Had you known people like your master and mistress before you went there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, and anyway I told you I used to go there on a Saturday. To work. Yes, I'm sure I used to go there when I was ten. I'm not quite sure thought. Oh I was very pleased to go, getting a shilling for going. Yes, I was allowed to stay t
here on odd saturdays and stay there all through the day on Sunday and come down to the school on Monday. That was a really good treat. But - my mother had to know about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did you think of the way that they lived? How did you see it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh
 I saw it as - very interesting. Quite a bit more interesting than today. With these televisions and things. There wasn't - there weren't even wirelesses then. No, nothing. Everyone was - joining in conversations in the house. There was no - there was no 
-
 no one had heard of the television then. Well I mean it hadn't been invented had it. I can remember - the first time that the wireless came over there. There was this old man, Morris Richards, who lived in Camarthy, he came down to Llan and - they put th
e wireless on to give him - to give him a treat really. And he said, stop that thing, it's getting on my nerves. He'd never heard it before. He just preferred to talk. To talk about the sheep and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were the manners and the ways of behav
ing of the masters and mistress in any way different from those of your family or your friends in Garreg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no. The same. But we had to be - gentlemanly. Yes, we used that polite form of you. But there was no such thing as sir or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You said you went to work in the forestry after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 That was run by the Board of Trade. I got more - wages there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh I got it through a cousin. He got it for me. He was working there before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - you fed the horses in the morning and then we went out to drag logs and then we bought the horses in and fed them at midday. And then I went from there, away from the horses, I went to a contract job making
 pit props to go down to the south. Yes, making props on a contract, it was a penny ha'penny or tuppence a prop. That I was paid. Yes, to go down to the south, we used to make quite good money. Two cousins, you know, us two cousins. The two of us were tog
ether on that. Yes I liked it very much there but - I got the sack from there after the boys came back from the war. They took the jobs. They took their jobs back I suppose. And we had to go back to the farm. That was in 1918.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What hours did you work in the forestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh they were great - big hours - long hours, there too. We started seven in the morning, feeding that is. We fed until half past eight. And then we went in again about half past eleven and - fed 'til half past one. And then we worked
 'til five. In the - forest and then we'd feed again 'til - seven or half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Twelve hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes. And then we had to - use the chaff cutter for - I mean chaff the - food - for the - for six horses. No, there were eight, and four of us -
 eight horses and there were four of us working with them. Yes, we had to chaff with a small chaff cutter to cut up the - cut up the hay. And we used to chaff in the evenings. Turning the handle. That was quite a good job. No, not good, hard job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And this was after finishing work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, after we'd - after we'd been pulling the logs. And we had to feed the horses as well. Oh yes, it was a very hard world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you work on Sundays too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, not - not dragging the logs but just feeding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about Saturdays, did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh only in the morning. And then there was a top horseman there and he did it on Saturday afternoons. Oh yes, we did it alternately. I'd do it one Saturday and he'd do it another one and there were four
 of us and we shared it out. That is Saturday afternoon and Sunday. And - yes, we had it so we worked Saturday afternoon and Sunday once a month. Yes, I mean it was - interesting that way. Oh and it was very hard, we - we had to go - or get the sack of co
urse. But then it wasn't possible to get work after that, so we were glad to go anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You didn't have holidays with pay or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How much did you get paid in the forestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I mean - you mean in a week or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You told me you had tuppence a prop?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I got a lot more money than I got on the farm. Yes, I mean sometimes I used to get seven or eight pounds in a week. Well that wasn't bad for those days was it. Yes, but I
 had to work hard for that, hard - working on a contract with a lot of hours. Especially on the props. You see, the more props we made the more money we got. We might work from seven o'clock in the morning 'til nine o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel that the wages were fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes. They were very fair - compared with the farm. 'Cos by this time we got - only got a pound a week on the farm. It had come up to a pound by then. Yes, by - by the time of the war it was a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And you were paid weekly on the farms by now were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I suppose that was a lot better than getting paid every six months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well, yes. But then if you were on the farm - what you did sometimes was, if things went very hard was to ask for a sub. I m
ean, if you - were getting twenty-six pounds in half a year, well may be you'd ask - during that time for four or five pounds because you had to have pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When you were still in the forestry did you still give your money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I did, I didn't give it all mind you. No, I paid for my food and things. I mean she had to have it didn't she. 'Cos she was the one that made my food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 So you lived at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes. Oh no, no, I lodged up at the forestry but she still made 
my food. Yes, I went up there on a - on a Monday. With a wallet on my back and a bike. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You'd lodge up in the forestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I'll tell you where it was, it's where Tom Kindeys' bought a house. Yes, up there. Plas Hafodhandrach. There was a b
ig crowd of us there. Goodness, we had fun. Yes, we had great fun. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 So you got on very well with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did your employer treat you, in the forest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, excellently. Yes, we called him the time
keeper. The - he was a very kind man. If we were a bit behind though he did tend to tell us off. If we were about ten minutes behind. Or late. But not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you on the whole get an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ry with him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no. We just said, you know, we were sorry for being late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How did you feel towards the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh I liked it well enough. In fact I'd have liked to have worked in the forestry for many years after this rather than go onto the farm. I did in fact go to the quarries but - I didn't like it there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You went to the quarry after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 By this time had you begun to regret the fact that you'd left school when you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I had a lot. Oh yes, if I'd stuck it - I mean I didn't - now I didn't see my
self as very much of a scholar. And I saw other boys who'd got ahead and - but still, that's how it goes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean after I was in the forestry? Yes, I worked in different places then until I went to - to there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 And you did go to the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, yes, but only for three weeks. And then I went to Erw Fawr, to work with the horses there, taking the - the slates down to Portmadoc. From the quarry down to Portmadoc. And then in the afternoo
ns I'd work on the land. Ploughing and that. Cattle and things. Then I went to be a farm labouerer in - Brynkir. That was a very good place. There was six of us working - there. And that's when we slept in the stable loft. It was a very good place and goo
d
 food there too. I mean, it was old fashioned food. That was the only place we had brwas. I don't know if you know what brwas is. You know the - the things they used to use to make - make butter, old fashioned things, not? Before churns. Well - we used to
 
eat - you know, it was something very like this and they'd fill this - this container up with brewas and there'd be six of us round this dish and - and they'd eat out of this but be'd leave a small fiece of brwas in between each persons section so we didn
't in fact eat - eat each other's. Yes, there was one person there and another one there and everyone had his - had his spoon. It was great fun. I couldn't get enough of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What sort of thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh it was - hard bread, rye bread. Which had been broken up very small and then it - you had a sort of - beef stock poured over it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 A sort of clear soup you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, a sort of soup that's been prepared at home. Yes, I mean, imagine if you boiled - pork or beef - and the juice from that 
would be poured over the bread crumbs. Oh it was very good. And I used to eat very quickly so I could get a - so the others'd get a bit less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Looking back on your life would you have prefer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ed to do a different job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, looking back I wouldn't. 
I've enjoyed myself as it has been. I mean, I liked the way they were. I remember an old farm which was rather bad for food and it's a story about a verse, a verse from the Bible. One morning - I tell you this is a real story, it's a true story, but I'm n
o
t going to name where it comes from, but you know very well which farm it is. There was a houseman there, a - a top - servant, top worker on a farm. Yes, he was the man who looked after the second farm servant, he was the top farm servant. And then there 
w
as a - a little - a little servant, a young servant, a young boy. Well - a young boy - a new young boy came at the beginning of the term, in May, and he was to work through 'til November. And then this manager bloke said - said to the little boy, remember
 
you have to learn a verse by - tomorrow morning, before breakfast, to say it at breakfast. And the little boy, said well I can't because you know I'm totally illeterate, as it was in those days, a long time ago. I can't. Well, never mind, we'l teach you o
n
e, they said. And so they taught him the verse and then tomorrow came, I don't know if you know about - these - verses in Welsh in the Bible. I'm sure you can translate them though, it's in the Bible. The verse is trwy dwys dy wynek y cie fara. I think th
e
 English translations, he who does not work, neither shall he eat, but literally it means, through the sweat of your face you get bread. And the little boy replied, tryw diwys dy wynek iy cie fara. And then the next day the little boy came out with his ve
rse. He said - we must get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207  better by God. And it was a ref}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
erence to the fact that there was very little butter on the bread on the table. And he was complaining about - I mean, he was rel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ting the verse to the lack of butter on the bread. And then - John Hu
ges said, not - on bread alone - man can't live by bread alone. Which may have been the verse he intended to say in the beginning. And the little boys says, by God we must get butter. But I mean wasn't that an awful thing to say in the company of the mast
er and mistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What happened to him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh they knew very well that the - the headman had - taught it to him. And then there was another time when we were given an enormous plate, it was pudding - pudding. And - it - pudding, rice pudding in fact
. And there was an enormous plate and a tiny bit of rice pudding. And the little boy said to the - said - mistress back, puzzle find the pudding. And then the next day, the plates were full of pudding, because the mistress didn't like that the boy had sai
d this the other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245772\charrsid16455207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
day. The plates were full of pudding. And he said, dear mistress, puzzle find the plate. And I mean, they're true you see. That's what's good in them. He was a real character, he didn't - didn't give a damn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 Did you ever serv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207  an apprenticeship or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Or any training or anything title that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, nothing like that. The only thing I was taught was a bit about how to deal with sheep, you know about that. Things like earmarking them. Shearing them. Yes, things l
ike that, that's the greatest craft hat I have. In fact, the - the greatest craft is - is - is my ability to remember the different earmarks of different flocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever have to help with delivering lambs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, I've done that all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Not even in the forestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, I didn't, I wasn't offered but I - I didn't take - I - I refused to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I don't know. Yes, I'll tell you why, the thing was that
 the others wouldn't come with me. The group I was with. And I didn't want to go by myself. But maybe you know, I - if - apart from that I would have gone. Only I wanted someone to join in with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Were there a lot of people that didn't join, didn't want to join at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, yes, a lot. I mean, but there was a trades union for agricultural workers then. But - very few people joined. Because - you ask why. Well this is my mind. My opinion. Well you see, the master wouldn't look on you in 
the same way. That was the sort of thoughts at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You were afraid of losing your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, we were afraid of losing our jobs. There was - no one had heard of a - stike or anything. We were afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you know anyone who joined the agricultural union, agricultural labourers union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I knew some, but they were very unhappy. In fact they left the farms and looked for jobs in the quarry. They didn't receive the same respect on the farms, they didn't look up to them as much
. Maybe we were wrong but that's what we thought at that time. But, you know, they didn't last long you know after they joined the union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that farm servants and employers or workers and employers had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh you mean interests in their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Not so much in their work, did you feel at that time that the employers were trying to extract as much as possible out of the servant?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes. Yes, they were definitely. But - but you must listen to this. I mean, the ol
d farm workers had much more interest in farming that - the - of that the master had. It was worth seeing them, you know, tidying up, specially tidying up in the hayfield, making hayricks. Thatching them, roofing them, they're worth seeing. They took grea
t
 pride in their work. And in that case the farm worker was - a step above or a - in a - in a position above the master in terms of work. But then the master was very pleased to see this. Because long ago I mean each farm used to compete with each other - 
compete - for the best hay rice, or the best p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 ough }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
 ploughing. To see who could do the tidiest job. And of course it was all ploughing with horses and - oh I suppose you wanted them to get - people had to get as straight a line as possible. Yes, yes, it had to go dead straight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 In the society would you say that the employers and workers had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well - I mean, if the - farm workers pleased, they - they - they lived as one with the employer. But, you know, if for instance, if a - a
 farmworker only stayed for six month, well then the employer didn't think much of this man. But if he pleased then - the employer would do everything to get this man to to remain with him. Would even give him more money. But, you know, then there were a 
few farmworkers who wouldn't stay, because maybe they didn't like it there. They just wanted to go. But - me, I mean, I've been one for staying really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that there was a greater division between employer and worker say in the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, well you see, I didn't like it in the quarry and I would prefer a master from the land rather than in the quarry. 'Cos they were more snobby in the quarry. The stewards and things. I mean that's what I'd say but I don't know very much about the quar
ry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 I suppose you pick this up thou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 gh through talking to quarrymen}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207  and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, and when I think of the poor creatures who used to walk up from Llanfrothen up to Rhosydd - and it's a bit of away, I mean, it's four miles and they had to up there by seven. And I know of some, and my father for one. He was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 going up to Rhosydd and he arri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
ved ten minutes late and was turned back. He lost a day. Yes, arrive - if they arrive after the hooter it's finished. And my father was there ten minutes late and 
there was this old Evan Jones the steward who sent him down and told him to come back tomorrow morning. And be there by seven and maybe you'd get a job. But - and he went the next day and he arrived there promptly at seven o'clock. Goodness me, it was a r
eally terrible time. I mean, I didn't like it - I told you that. I was afraid of that old bridge, the bridge that went - that collapsed under my - cousin, the one I told you about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you know what sort of wages they got in the quarry at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well I'm afraid I don't actually, I should know though. I've heard Idris say many times. Yes, they were paid a basic wage every week, and then at the end of the month they got a sort of bonus thing, depending on how productive they'd been. Yes, and they
 were paid extra when there was - they found a good seam of rock. It was called - this payment was called pen - pen mis. In fact it was Tal Pen Mis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you feel there was a difference of interest between workers at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, there
 was great competition. Proud. That's what they were, they were proud. And then others weren't. Yes, they were very proud of their work, I've told you about the - the - hayricks. But then again no one was jealous or anything like - that. I mean, I was a f
a
rmworker and I'd make a hay stack but - I wasn't very good at it. And then I'd see someone else doing one and I'd be proud of his job. I didn't feel mean towards him. Yes, I was never jealous. And I was pleased to see someone doing it. I mean, I could mak
e a haystack and I could put the roof on it but - it didn't please me. It wasn't good enough for me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you remember then a great division between craftsmen and labourers, not on the farm anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, on the farm we were all much of the same level. That's what I would say a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6713988\charrsid16455207 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 yway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Would you say that working has changed your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I would. What - you mean - has it changed to be - now to be working short hours, eight hour days and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 How do you feel work has affected you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Yes, I mean it - it certainly has affected - affected my life. The thing - the thing is about nowadays is that people - people don't have so much pleasure. They don't have so much pleasure to work on a - farm, they don't have so muc
h commitment to the work. And way round here that is. Yes, I suppose they just see it as a - as a job - yes, it's just a job to get money, big money. So you finish the job and move on. There are very few people who have - have - take an interest in say fe
eding the cattle through the winter and doing things with the little calves and things. And very few are capable of - well, being vets and pulling claves - obstructed calves out of the mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You went away to live on the farm after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But then I used to go home every Saturday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I was much - I felt - much more for them afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your brothers and sister, did that relationship change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Well yes, I mean my sister went away to work in Liverpool. And I mean that did change me a lot because I was very glad to see her when she came home. And then my older brother went - went to work in the south, to the coal pits. And I mean we were v
ery pleased to see him - coming back. But I never went away so far that I couldn't come back every week or every fortnight. And - I got on well with my mother and father and it was good to be able to talk to them about my feelings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was Sunday any different to what it had been when you'd been at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, I saw Sunday very different in the - in the beginning. Because - I had to work in the mornings in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 But you still went on going to chapel and everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you take an interest in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
No, no, not - not very much. And I mean I still don't today. I mean, I go to vote but - but that's it. I put a little cross where - where I think it should go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Do you put it anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, I take it very slowly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Can you say what you do vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, I think I'd better not say. I'll tell you after we've stopped the tape recorder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You didn't vote at all before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh no, no, no, I was too young. Because I mean it was twenty-one that you had to be then wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you still spend your free time in the same way after you'd left home and gone to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 You mean, in the evenings? No, it didn't change me for a long time. I used
 to come down to Garreg to play, exactly the same, with the boys there. And I was really frightened of going back up to Foty after that. Yes, and - after I been playing and I had to go up past that old shaft you know where you can hear the waters dripping
 down, I was frightened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you make any new friends with girls or boys of the same age as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 
Oh yes, I made great friends with a boy from Tynygrissiau. Yes, his name was Dick, he's died a long time now. And I'd go over to Tanygrisiau and have tea with him - on a Sunday. That is in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Which day did you go, did you go up over the mountain through Rhosydd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, we'd go to Tan-y-Bwlch and walk along the railway line. Through the big tunnel, that way. We'd walk along the rail
s, that's what we'd do. Holding each other's shoulders.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did you take these new friends you made home with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes I did. Yes, I used to go over to Tanygrisiau and Dic would come down to Gareg to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went away with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I had to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Even after you went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes I did, I had to. I had to tell every move to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 When you were staying at home did you have to be in at any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh yes, yes, I had to be in the house by about ten. I couldn't be very late. Yes, I mean it was fairly restricting really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What about your brothers, what jobs did they do altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Well, my younger brother, he worked on the farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 All through his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, all through his life. And the other one, the older one, he worked in the south mostly. Yes, he was down in the pits all his life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Was he the one that died of T.B.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 No, no, it's my younger bro
ther that died of T.B. My older brother died of cancer. And my sister died of T.B. And my sister was only twenty-seven. But my younger brother was older, he was about forty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Did your sister ever marry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Yes, yes, do you remember No John from Port
? You know, the one that drives the lorries. Well his - his wife is - is - the daughter of my sister, Megan. And then theres Mayra who lives In Llanroost who married Watkin Coytee. And she's he sister of Megan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 What did your sister's husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh he worked in the quarry. Yes, in Rosydd and Croesor. Yes, he worked alternately there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10362445 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Is that what he did all his life?
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid10362445 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023162 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14947165\charrsid16455207 Oh - yes, but - but - no, he's still alive - he's living in Liverpool. Yes, he's remarried but - I've no idea what he's doing now.
\par }}